ast Village neighborhood of Manhattan."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Six days short of seventy-eight","body":"Born in Manhattan on October 13, 1727, he died there on October 7, 1805 — six days short of his birthday. His 1764 marriage to Margaret Livingston, granddaughter of the first lord of Livingston Manor, had united two of colonial New York’s great dynasties."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Stuyvesant_(merchant)"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"peter-stuyvesant-1727"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM431","name":"Saint Marks Church-in-the-Bowery Churchyard","location":{"city":"New York","county":"New York County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/641176/saint-marks-church-in-the-bowery-churchyard","notes":"Stuyvesant family burial site in East Village Manhattan.","hooker_connections":["H02005","I00904","X03076"]},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}